1
00:00:28,666 --> 00:00:30,000
[SHIRO GRUNTS]

2
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:35,250
[EXPLOSION]

3
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:39,000
[GROUP GASPS]

4
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:49,458
Ganta, I'm so
glad you're okay.

5
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:57,250
Close, huh?

6
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,750
You...
You little...

7
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:02,666
Dear god...
The chip...

8
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:04,041
What did
you just do?

9
00:01:04,125 --> 00:01:04,958
Hmm...?

10
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:06,666
I was on my way
to find Ganta...

11
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:09,000
but there was this
person who... I'd never...

12
00:01:09,083 --> 00:01:11,916
[ENDOU] You're in bed with that
mother-fucking monk, aren't you?

13
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,333
Aren't you?!

14
00:01:13,416 --> 00:01:14,833
[ENDOU GRUNTS ANGRILY]

15
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:18,041
Huh? But I'm not in bed...

16
00:01:18,125 --> 00:01:20,541
[GANTA]
How could you...?

17
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:25,291
Everything was riding
on that chip... Everything...

18
00:01:25,375 --> 00:01:28,083
They entrusted me with it... 

19
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:32,041
I was... I was
their last hope.

20
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:33,166
Last hope...?

21
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:34,791
No, that stupid chip
was too dangerous

22
00:01:34,875 --> 00:01:37,291
for you to be
carrying by yourself!

23
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:40,666
Goddamn it, I know
what I signed up for!

24
00:01:40,750 --> 00:01:42,333
You're not my
damn babysitter!

25
00:01:42,416 --> 00:01:46,500
Well you're too weak
to be left on your own!

26
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:49,500
These meanies wanted
too much out of you!

27
00:01:52,041 --> 00:01:53,500
Are you completely mental?! 

28
00:01:53,583 --> 00:01:55,791
People laid down their lives
to get that thing out of here!

29
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:57,875
I don't care
about that stuff!

30
00:01:57,958 --> 00:02:00,875
Like anyone gives a damn
about your stupid little plan!

31
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:02,500
Without me you'd be--

32
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:06,333
[SHIRO GASPS]

33
00:02:11,791 --> 00:02:13,500
Get out...

34
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:16,208
I'm sick and tired
of your shit!

35
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:20,958
[FOOTSTEPS]

36
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:26,000
♪ opening song ♪

37
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:56,541
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

38
00:03:56,625 --> 00:03:57,583
[GROUP GASPS]

39
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,000
[BELL CHIMES]

40
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:02,083
[KARAKO BREATHES HEAVILY]

41
00:04:02,166 --> 00:04:02,833
Karako!

42
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:03,708
You made it!

43
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,125
Oh hell yeah!
Heh, heh...

44
00:04:05,208 --> 00:04:06,666
Heh...

45
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,708
I think I get it...

46
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:13,666
So our powers don't 
really work against 'em.

47
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,875
I am surprised about
your little friend, though.

48
00:04:15,958 --> 00:04:17,916
Didn't peg her for a mole.

49
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,458
No... That's
not what's up...

50
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:22,083
She's been a
clueless little dingbat

51
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:24,125
since we were
both children.

52
00:04:24,208 --> 00:04:28,500
Still, though... I never thought
she'd do something like that.

53
00:04:28,583 --> 00:04:30,750
[KARAKO] So we're
all that's left, huh?

54
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:33,125
Guess we royally
screwed the pooch.

55
00:04:34,916 --> 00:04:37,291
Well... Good thing
there's still time...

56
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:39,333
The inspection party
hasn't packed it in yet.

57
00:04:39,416 --> 00:04:40,208
[GROUP GASPS]

58
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:41,958
What are you
talking about?

59
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:43,875
What have we got
left up our sleeve?

60
00:04:43,958 --> 00:04:46,708
[KARAKO] Plenty.
Unless you're ready to quit.

61
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,875
Hey, nobody said
nothing 'bout quitting.

62
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:51,708
Yeah, but what are we capable
of without the data chip?

63
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,833
Plus Rokuro's MIA...

64
00:04:53,916 --> 00:04:56,708
I know... But the chip's
not our only resource...

65
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:59,958
Hell no. There are a number of
ways to get our voice out there.

66
00:05:00,041 --> 00:05:02,291
All we have to do is make
sure the federal inspectors

67
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:04,833
catch wind of what's really
going on behind the scenes.

68
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:06,416
Of course...!

69
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,500
If one of us can make it to 'em,
then the cat's out of the bag!

70
00:05:08,583 --> 00:05:09,750
[WAKABAYASHI]
They'd listen if they saw

71
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,000
a Branch of Sin in action.

72
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:13,125
Proof of our plight
in the flesh!

73
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:14,666
That is what we're gonna do.

74
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,291
The only thing that's
changed about the plan 

75
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:18,791
is what we're doin' to get
our message out to the public.

76
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:21,833
And they'll need a lot more than
some goddamn robot to stop us.

77
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:24,875
So... now what...
are you the new boss?

78
00:05:24,958 --> 00:05:25,791
[KARAKO]
Guess again.

79
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:27,083
[GROUP] Huh...?

80
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:29,916
Nagi is still alive.
I can feel it in my bones.

81
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,416
The monk won't kill him.

82
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,250
[GROUP GASPS]

83
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,583
He's still our leader...

84
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:38,333
And I'm gonna fight to my
last breath for that man!

85
00:05:38,416 --> 00:05:43,166
[GUITAR CHORD RINGS OUT]

86
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,708
You been great! Thank you!

87
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:47,250
So, if you had to choose,

88
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:50,041
which of those lil' ditties
rocked your socks off the most?

89
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:52,916
They both make we want
to puncture my eardrums.

90
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,083
[GENKAKU] Ha! Flattery
will get you everywhere.

91
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:59,166
What the hell's the point
in keeping me alive...?

92
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:01,000
They'll... They'll just...

93
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:03,000
[GENKAKU] Enough of this
high school shit, huh...?

94
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:06,875
Strappin' guy like you's
meant for better things.

95
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:11,000
Come on... Be all that
you can be... Wake up!

96
00:06:12,291 --> 00:06:15,541
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

97
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:17,041
Okay, access
is granted.

98
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,541
Perfect... 

99
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:21,583
We have an hour before the
inspection team wraps things up.

100
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:24,458
Extract everything you can from
the hard drive and secure it.

101
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:26,041
Kind of off-topic,
ma'am, but...

102
00:06:26,125 --> 00:06:28,708
Seriously,
what's your secret?

103
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:31,791
Hot sake for breakfast and
red wine with every meal...

104
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:33,458
A porterhouse
for dessert...

105
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,750
Stay on task, Kasuga.

106
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:36,916
Stop gawking.

107
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,083
[KASUGA]
Yes ma'am!

108
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:41,250
[MAKINA THINKING]
What the hell is this...?

109
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,750
"Prisoner Suitability?"

110
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:44,833
[MAKINA GASPS]

111
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:46,416
Take cover!

112
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:47,875
Take cover where?!

113
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,791
Huh... What an
interesting office.

114
00:06:56,875 --> 00:06:58,333
All for privacy...

115
00:06:58,416 --> 00:07:01,833
Sanctuary is indispensible for
the solvent mind, you know.

116
00:07:01,916 --> 00:07:03,875
Besides, should
one need to vent...

117
00:07:03,958 --> 00:07:05,750
solitude is absolutely vital.

118
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,875
[AOHI]
Looks like a daycare.

119
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:11,208
So tell me about production...

120
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:12,875
As you know,
outright synthesis

121
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:14,708
of the nameless
worm eludes us...

122
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:17,250
But, we have found that
Branch of Sin wielders

123
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,333
seem able to
infect non-users.

124
00:07:19,416 --> 00:07:20,666
[AOHI] Go on.

125
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,416
[MAKINA THINKING]
Secretary Ahoi...?

126
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,625
What does he mean
by "production"?

127
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:26,541
Surely they're not...

128
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:27,916
[AOHI] That said...

129
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,000
If the new copies
were to run amok beyond 

130
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,750
the Defense Ministry's
current jurisdiction...

131
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,833
"In for a penny,
in for a pound..." 

132
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:37,791
My dear sir, such risks are
the cost of doing business... 

133
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:39,750
We daren't falter.

134
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,833
[AOHI] There will be
no change in your budget.

135
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:44,458
[TAMAKI] Heh, heh, heh... 
Heartless skinflint...

136
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,000
The ladies must adore you.

137
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:49,125
[MAKINA THINKING]
"Suitability..." Of course!

138
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:55,666
Well you're too weak to
look be left on your own!

139
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:56,875
[GANTA THINKING]
Dumbass.

140
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,541
It's not enough you
screw up our mission;

141
00:07:58,625 --> 00:08:00,708
you gotta spout off
crap like that?!

142
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,750
Man, fuck her.

143
00:08:02,833 --> 00:08:04,625
[OHARA] Funny how no
one's cracked down on us

144
00:08:04,708 --> 00:08:07,250
after the stunt we just tried
to pull, don't you think?

145
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,916
I mean, they've had the time.

146
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,791
Those little bastards prefer
us all on pins and needles.

147
00:08:11,875 --> 00:08:13,291
What's their game?

148
00:08:13,375 --> 00:08:15,500
They could've squelched us
all in a heartbeat, you know...

149
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:17,041
If they haven't,
then chances are

150
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,708
they're just trying to smoke
out the source of our intel...

151
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,875
"Game" is the operative
word, my dear.

152
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,250
Oh, great...

153
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:24,708
They're just doing this
just for shits and giggles.

154
00:08:24,791 --> 00:08:26,333
What would you guys
feel about enlisting

155
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:28,000
some high profile inmate?

156
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:30,083
Not just someone likely
to grab headlines...

157
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:32,750
but someone who might be
able to help save our asses.

158
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,791
[KARAKO] Nobody fits the bill
better than Crow, but he's out.

159
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,458
What about asking Hummingbird?

160
00:08:37,541 --> 00:08:40,375
Little too schizoid
for my taste.

161
00:08:40,458 --> 00:08:41,750
There's the Albatross.

162
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,125
[ENDOU]
That dude's a relic...

163
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:45,583
But hey, bet we could
get King Fisher in on this.

164
00:08:45,666 --> 00:08:48,083
[WAKABAYASHI] Not unless
you can raise the dead.

165
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:51,458
Oh, man... that's a swift
kick in the nuts, huh? 

166
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:52,833
How 'bout Mockingbird?

167
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:54,750
[GROUP] Aahh!

168
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,833
Now there's a good
bird to have!

169
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:58,625
All the damage
he could do!

170
00:08:58,708 --> 00:09:02,250
Yeah... If anyone could actually
track down where he is...

171
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:05,916
Hey, uh... I'm not too
shabby, you know... 

172
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,416
I know I'm not on their
level, but... I could... try.

173
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:12,208
[KARAKO] You're family,
kid, but... I mean...

174
00:09:12,291 --> 00:09:15,416
Unless you know somethin' about
taking down the Undertakers...

175
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,125
[GANTA GASPS]

176
00:09:17,208 --> 00:09:18,458
Nothing personal...

177
00:09:18,541 --> 00:09:21,291
It's just that we need
someone with experience...

178
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:24,083
We really can't afford to
get it wrong a second time... 

179
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,958
Not to sell you short
or anything, but...

180
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:27,166
Well, you know.

181
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:28,958
Nah... I get you...

182
00:09:29,041 --> 00:09:32,625
S'just... We're in this mess
to begin with because of me...

183
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:38,791
I mean... If I'd just...
kept Shiro out of all of this...

184
00:09:38,875 --> 00:09:40,208
[GANTA]
You guys depended on me...

185
00:09:40,291 --> 00:09:43,708
...and I let you down.
They're dead... and for what?

186
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:47,208
[KARAKO] Really...? Keep
talkin' like that, Ganta... 

187
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:51,166
It's a good way of
gettin' your ass kicked.

188
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:52,541
[GANTA THINKING] C'mon...

189
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:55,041
I'm trying to apologize here...

190
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:56,916
What else can I do?

191
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,875
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

192
00:09:57,958 --> 00:09:59,666
[GROUP GASPS]

193
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:01,000
[WAKABAYASHI] Rokuro!

194
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:02,916
[ENDOU]
Holy shit, you're alive! 

195
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:03,833
[OHARA]
Are you hurt?!

196
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:05,875
Hold on... Where's Nagi?

197
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:08,791
[GROUP GASPS]

198
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:11,625
Tell me...

199
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:13,666
Which of you...
...fuck heads...

200
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:18,083
...shat on...
...my goddamn bomb?!

201
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:20,416
Which of you mother-fucking
geniuses guessed

202
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:24,083
the data chip was
an incendiary device?

203
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:26,458
Hey... Calm the hell
down, dude; it's us.

204
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:29,708
Hold the damn phone...
You made the chip?!

205
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:31,500
Can you be
that stupid...?!

206
00:10:31,583 --> 00:10:33,125
It's called betrayal...

207
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:35,958
There was never any magical
super-secret data chip... 

208
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:39,166
It was supposed to
kill you dumb asses!

209
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,875
Do you have any idea

210
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,500
how much it pisses me off
that you're not dead?!

211
00:10:43,583 --> 00:10:44,708
What the...

212
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,916
You had to have
known all this...

213
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,708
How'd a bunch of blind fucks 
like you manage to survive?

214
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:53,500
You actually got
rid of it on accident?

215
00:10:53,583 --> 00:10:54,833
[GANTA GASPS]

216
00:11:00,916 --> 00:11:02,916
Guess dumb luck
favors the dumb...

217
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,291
But it might come in handy for
what I got in mind for you now.

218
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:10,250
Seriously... Me...
Join a gang like yours...

219
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,166
You're out of your mind to ask.

220
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,750
[GENKAKU] What is it with
you always shuttin' me down?

221
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,833
It's been two years.

222
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:18,625
Two years... Yes...

223
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:20,125
[GENKAKU] But all the
Undertakers are playin'

224
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:22,625
a few cards short
of a full deck...

225
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:24,666
It's how the worm turns.

226
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:25,958
[NAGI GRUNTS]

227
00:11:26,041 --> 00:11:28,041
And you're the
craziest of 'em all.

228
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:30,500
I've seen your
work firsthand, Owl.

229
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:33,916
Why else would I be
so passionately devoted?

230
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,083
You murdered her!

231
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:39,375
My wife...
You murdered her!!!

232
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:40,583
[NAGI SCREAMS]

233
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:41,833
Yeah, but I haven't murdered

234
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:44,250
your little
clubhouse gang yet...

235
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,541
Well, at least
not all of 'em...

236
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:52,041
But the gig's just getting
started, my lovely.

237
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:54,166
As of this moment,
you're all hostages...

238
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,291
Till Nagi sees the
error of his ways.

239
00:11:56,375 --> 00:11:59,791
Soon they'll be executed,
one by one.

240
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:01,208
[KARAKO GASPS]

241
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:02,833
You fucking traitor!

242
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:10,333
[CRACKING]

243
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,791
[ROKURO] Now then...

244
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:15,833
Which of you is the best
way to make my point?

245
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:19,375
[GANTA GASPS]

246
00:12:19,458 --> 00:12:21,875
Your sniveling little
mug gets on my nerves...

247
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:26,791
So whaddya say to helping me
revise my calculations... noob?

248
00:12:35,541 --> 00:12:38,791
[TOTO] Someone is
calling out for help...

249
00:12:38,875 --> 00:12:42,500
The data chip your friend
is carrying will explode.

250
00:12:42,583 --> 00:12:45,083
[SHIRO]
Data chip?

251
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:48,291
Hmph...! Ganta's a meanie!

252
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:51,083
Ugh! Who cares
about him anyway?! 

253
00:12:51,166 --> 00:12:53,791
Hey, Grandpa!
Where are you?!

254
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:56,083
Oh, wait...
He's probably still asleep... 

255
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:58,875
Whatever. I know where
you hide the goodies!

256
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,416
[SHIRO] These are
really all just for me?

257
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,625
[DIRECTOR]
All for you...

258
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:08,625
Enjoy them at your
leisure, my snowflake.

259
00:13:08,708 --> 00:13:11,291
I don't think Ganta knows
he's coming back home yet...

260
00:13:11,375 --> 00:13:13,291
But when he does I'm
gonna share them with him!

261
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:16,125
See, Mama... always told
me that friends share!

262
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:20,000
Oh, hey! Ha! Ganta always loved
these ones the very best... 

263
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:22,666
The almond makes it hard
to break in half, though... 

264
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:26,166
He can have it to himself...
cuz I like the star ones!

265
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:28,791
It's so wonderful
to have you here.

266
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:33,208
Let us drown out those painful
echoes of the past together.

267
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:37,375
Time need no longer
be our prison...

268
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:39,375
Are you happy, my dear?

269
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:41,041
[SHIRO]
Mm-hmm...!

270
00:13:42,458 --> 00:13:46,041
[SHIRO] Well, guess who doesn't
have to share with you anymore?

271
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:47,958
Not the chocolate...

272
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:49,333
Or the one with honey...

273
00:13:49,416 --> 00:13:52,166
And most especially
not the star!

274
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:01,291
Mmmm...
Nummers!

275
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:15,125
[SHIRO CRIES]

276
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:16,458
[ROKURO LAUGHS]

277
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:19,708
Oh yeah...! How wicked
is this?! I get to be bad!

278
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:22,541
And you, kiddo, get to be the
first of the bloody valentines 

279
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:25,541
that twist Nagi's mind
to our way of thinking!

280
00:14:25,625 --> 00:14:28,250
[GANTA THINKING] My Branch of
Sin doesn't work on these guys.

281
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,083
I'm dead!

282
00:14:30,166 --> 00:14:32,458
Bastard! I knew
we couldn't trust you!

283
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:34,291
Hey, no cutting in
line, queen bee...

284
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:38,041
You'll have your turn when
I'm done with the drone here.

285
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:39,958
[GANTA THINKING]
We're all gonna die...

286
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:41,333
Oh, god!

287
00:14:41,416 --> 00:14:42,833
I never got to ask you
what you thought of

288
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:45,041
the video that leaked
out during your trial...

289
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:46,375
You know the one, dontcha?

290
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:49,791
Oh, yeah... Heh...
That was yours truly, dude.

291
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,333
[GANTA GASPS]

292
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:53,625
Not even a minute long,

293
00:14:53,708 --> 00:14:55,666
and the world was
ready to pummel you...

294
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:58,125
I didn't really think it'd be
that effective, to be honest.

295
00:14:58,208 --> 00:15:00,166
Sure fucks with your
chances of living longer

296
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:03,125
than a day if you ever
get out of this joint, huh?

297
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:04,375
[GANTA YELLS]

298
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:05,833
[ROKURO LAUGHS]

299
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:07,666
Killer moves you
got there, Woodpecker!

300
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:10,291
I totally see what all
the noise is about!

301
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:13,625
Hey... uglies... Chop-chop.

302
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,666
[ROKURO] You ever hear
the legend 'bout that girl

303
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:23,583
who dumped her unwanted
baby off the side of a mountain?

304
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:26,166
You know: she was all
tryin' to make some cash 

305
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,750
to send back home to her family

306
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:30,583
and didn't have
time to raise a kid...

307
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:35,958
[BABY CRIES]

308
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:39,708
Then, ten years later,
all these tweens and hikers

309
00:15:39,791 --> 00:15:41,208
started disappearing
in the woods...

310
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:43,125
Bunch of trackers sent
in with their dogs 

311
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:46,375
to try and sniff 'em out
wound up getting butchered.

312
00:15:46,458 --> 00:15:49,833
So they find the creature
responsible and, drum roll,

313
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:53,791
it's the baby all grown up.

314
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:56,083
The thing's lair was
wall-to-wall bodies:

315
00:15:56,166 --> 00:15:59,333
heads on spikes, torsos
dangling from meat hooks,

316
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:01,333
arms and legs piled
all over the floor

317
00:16:01,416 --> 00:16:03,083
like a mannequin factory...

318
00:16:03,166 --> 00:16:04,875
They also found
another creature.

319
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:06,791
One who friggin' hated
being dragged away

320
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:09,125
from his prized collection...

321
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:14,541
Turns out the baby
had made a friend...

322
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:17,416
An early victim he'd
decided not to kill,

323
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:18,458
and together they'd been making

324
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:21,250
fashion out of
lady bits for years.

325
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:24,125
I know you're thinking, sounds
too good to be true, right?

326
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,375
Well, allow me to introduce

327
00:16:25,458 --> 00:16:28,125
1st lieutenant Undertaker
Gozuchi Mouzuri...

328
00:16:28,208 --> 00:16:29,583
...and his trusty sidekick,

329
00:16:29,666 --> 00:16:32,000
2nd Lieutenant
Dohkoko Sinnagawa!

330
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:34,500
Otherwise known
as your executioners!

331
00:16:34,583 --> 00:16:35,416
Shiro.

332
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,708
[ROKURO LAUGHS]

333
00:16:36,791 --> 00:16:39,083
[CRACKING]

334
00:16:39,166 --> 00:16:41,541
Okay, let's see some
viscera, fellas!

335
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,791
Ah-one...! and ah-two!

336
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:46,041
[SENJI]
Dead center!

337
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:52,791
Three!

338
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:55,625
[SENJI] Damn it. How many
times I gotta tell you... 

339
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:57,583
If you're gonna play
warrior with your buddies... 

340
00:16:57,666 --> 00:16:59,458
Daddy wants a
piece of the pie.

341
00:16:59,541 --> 00:17:01,791
Now which of these
chumps is toughest?

342
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,958
Probably... those two.

343
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:08,958
[SENJI STAMMERS]

344
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:12,125
Senji... You
actually showed up.

345
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:13,458
[ELITE GUARD 10A]
Shit, it's Crow!

346
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:15,333
[ELITE GUARD 10B]
What's he got to do with this?!

347
00:17:15,416 --> 00:17:17,291
Make a break for it, people!

348
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:23,083
Ah, the hell with it...

349
00:17:23,166 --> 00:17:25,958
Peons are as good
as any, I suppose.

350
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:33,500
Heads up...! Their weapons
will neutralize your virus!

351
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:35,458
[ROKURO LAUGHS]

352
00:17:35,541 --> 00:17:37,208
[ROKURO] Idiot!

353
00:17:37,291 --> 00:17:39,791
Worm Eaters can blast oxidizing
accelerators in excess

354
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:42,291
of twenty mega-pascals per
unit of air pressure volume,

355
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:43,583
so good luck
catchin' em off guard

356
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,458
with your usual
shtick, asshole!

357
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:48,208
Oh man, and it's
not even my birthday!

358
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:49,583
[ROKURO LAUGHS]

359
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:52,250
Don't fuck with
the human calculator!

360
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:56,333
[SENJI]
Gotcha... So...

361
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,458
What if I do this?

362
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:13,041
Invisible black...
Read 'em and weep, bitches.

363
00:18:15,041 --> 00:18:18,125
Worm Eaters, huh...?
Won't be rememberin' that... 

364
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:20,166
Super-sonic blade's
all you need... 

365
00:18:20,250 --> 00:18:22,833
So adios...
Crow Claw saves the day.

366
00:18:22,916 --> 00:18:24,333
[ROKURO] Bullshit...!

367
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:27,958
You did not just get the drop
on them with a sonic boom!

368
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,166
Hardcore.

369
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,708
Is that
even possible?

370
00:18:30,791 --> 00:18:34,166
[GANTA THINKING]
Holy crap... He's amazing...

371
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:37,166
Like the exact opposite of me.

372
00:18:40,291 --> 00:18:42,125
Ganta...

373
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:45,541
You're such a dummy.

374
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,291
[LOUD THUD]

375
00:18:47,375 --> 00:18:48,916
Who's there?!

376
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,708
[TOTO LAUGHS]

377
00:18:50,791 --> 00:18:54,791
Oh, no one special...
Just an echo...

378
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:56,791
Heh... Well... So to speak.

379
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:57,791
Huh...?

380
00:18:58,750 --> 00:18:59,625
Oh!

381
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:02,458
Hmm...?
What's wrong?

382
00:19:02,541 --> 00:19:04,375
It was the data chip... 

383
00:19:04,458 --> 00:19:08,291
Ganta's upset with me.
I don't understand why.

384
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:11,458
[NAGI BREATHES HEAVILY]

385
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:14,083
Damn it...
Your resistance is insane.

386
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:15,916
So much for laying
bare that inner life

387
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,250
with a fine tooth comb, huh?

388
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:21,791
[NAGI]
Joke while you can.

389
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:26,791
The Scar Chain is going to bring
this sewer... to its knees.

390
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:31,250
You're... barking up
the wrong tree...

391
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:35,208
If you think... I'll ever
be an Undertaker... 

392
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:39,291
Mark my words,
this is the end of you.

393
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,416
My, aren't we
well-fed on delusion.

394
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:45,750
I envy your stamina man.

395
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:49,333
C'mon, just try to think
back... Visualize it... 

396
00:19:49,416 --> 00:19:52,750
Two years ago I murdered
your pretty little wife.

397
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:55,625
Not long after,
you went on a rampage...

398
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:58,041
Twenty-two of my
subordinates ended up 

399
00:19:58,125 --> 00:20:01,916
decorating the barracks
with their intestines.

400
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,875
[NAGI] Wha...?

401
00:20:03,958 --> 00:20:07,708
[GENKAKU] Let your mind
recapture the beauty of it all.

402
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,958
[NAGI] No... No...

403
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:13,000
[GENKAKU LAUGHS]

404
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:14,583
[NAGI] You lie!

405
00:20:14,666 --> 00:20:17,083
[GENKAKU] You should've seen
the locker I was hiding in;

406
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:19,125
There was as much as
my piss on the inside

407
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:23,875
as there was of their 
blood on the outside.

408
00:20:23,958 --> 00:20:29,166
You were so gorgeous in those
moments, Owl; a living god... 

409
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:32,541
Mercy's avatar.
Can't you see it?

410
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:36,708
[NAGI] This isn't my
memory! You put it there!

411
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:39,416
[GENKAKU] No one's blaming you
for blockin' it out, love...

412
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:40,583
In a sewer like this,

413
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:43,416
repression's how
a sane man copes.

414
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,958
But understand:

415
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:48,750
the Undertakers don't so much
want to have you as be you.

416
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:59,958
[GANTA]
Look at me: I'm an insect.

417
00:21:00,041 --> 00:21:02,875
She was really just
trying to protect me...

418
00:21:02,958 --> 00:21:04,958
...and I punched
her for it.

419
00:21:05,041 --> 00:21:06,625
I'm dirt.

420
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:10,666
And if Senji hadn't shown up...

421
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:12,875
I mean look at me,
for crying out loud...

422
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:16,791
I musta been out of my mind
thinking I could help.

423
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:20,166
I am weak... A stupid kid...

424
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:23,125
A liability to
everybody I like...

425
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:27,250
Hey...
That isn't you talking...

426
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:28,791
It's this damn place.

427
00:21:28,875 --> 00:21:32,875
We've all thought like that...
Comes with the territory...

428
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,750
With being here...
and that's why

429
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:37,666
Deadman Wonderland
has to be destroyed.

430
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,250
It's why we need friends...

431
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,875
...and allies like Crow
to help us level this place.

432
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:44,083
Please, Senji:
join the fight with us.

433
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:46,791
Come on man... We might
as well pack it in without you.

434
00:21:46,875 --> 00:21:49,583
Just think of the whoopass we
could wreak on these assholes!

435
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:53,041
[GANTA THINKING] They're right.
We'd actually stand a chance.

436
00:21:53,125 --> 00:21:55,291
[SENJI LAUGHS]

437
00:21:55,375 --> 00:21:59,250
You guys kill me! Fuuuuck no.

438
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:01,083
Think it's any different
on the outside...?

439
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:03,083
Cause, I got news for you...

440
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:05,291
There's this thing called
"survival of the fittest"

441
00:22:05,375 --> 00:22:07,375
that calls the shots
wherever you go.

442
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:09,708
Least here it's straightforward!

443
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:11,750
You're a just a pack
lookin' for an Alpha Male,

444
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:13,458
and I ain't interested...

445
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:14,958
Never will be.

446
00:22:15,916 --> 00:22:17,041
Don't bare your teeth

447
00:22:17,125 --> 00:22:20,875
'less you're ready
to bite down... hard.

448
00:22:20,958 --> 00:22:23,125
You're too
weak, Ganta!

449
00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,208
[TOTO] Pick yourself up
by the bootstraps...

450
00:22:42,291 --> 00:22:47,041
Oh my... This...
this is... very bizarre.

451
00:22:47,125 --> 00:22:49,291
It's going to take
some getting used to.

452
00:22:49,375 --> 00:22:51,125
[SHIRO]
Get used to going away.

453
00:22:51,208 --> 00:22:53,375
[TOTO]
Ah! That's what I wanted to say!

454
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:55,083
The name is now Toto...

455
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:57,625
but I'm also known
as... the Mockingbird.

456
00:22:57,708 --> 00:23:00,250
It's so nice to see you again.

457
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,833
Don't worry, my snowflake...

458
00:23:01,916 --> 00:23:05,791
I haven't the least
intention of hurting you.

459
00:23:05,875 --> 00:23:07,958
Never you...

460
00:23:08,041 --> 00:23:13,000
♪ closing song ♪

461
00:24:38,916 --> 00:24:40,666
[MAKINA]
A twisted smile carved

462
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:43,083
into the face of a
wrathful god...

463
00:24:43,166 --> 00:24:47,208
Blood-soaked tears and mangled
flesh blotting out the sky...

464
00:24:47,291 --> 00:24:48,875
Deadman Wonderland:

465
00:24:48,958 --> 00:24:52,958
a bird's nest running red with
the sins of its hatchlings...

